1361
00:55:25,000 --> 00:55:27,000
Covered chips in all-dressed chicken.

1362
00:55:27,000 --> 00:55:29,000
Honestly, 100% cut.

1363
00:55:29,000 --> 00:55:31,000
Egg wash to get it to stick.

1364
00:55:31,000 --> 00:55:33,000
Isn't it just

1365
00:55:33,000 --> 00:55:35,000
a savory panko?

1366
00:55:35,000 --> 00:55:37,000
Dinner tomorrow night, baby.

1367
00:55:37,000 --> 00:55:39,000
I got all-dressed chips.

1368
00:55:39,000 --> 00:55:41,000
Here we go.

1369
00:55:41,000 --> 00:55:43,000
Should never not have all-dressed chips.

1370
00:55:43,000 --> 00:55:45,000
Oh, I can't with the all-dressed chip.

1371
00:55:45,000 --> 00:55:47,000
Is it vinegary?

1372
00:55:47,000 --> 00:55:49,000
Is it ketchup?

1373
00:55:49,000 --> 00:55:51,000
It's all of those.

1374
00:55:51,000 --> 00:55:53,000
It's like a Dr. Pepper.

1375
00:55:53,000 --> 00:55:55,000
There's 23 flavors.

1376
00:55:55,000 --> 00:55:57,000
You can't pick out just the one.

1377
00:55:57,000 --> 00:55:59,000
Oh, no, I love Dr. Pepper.

1378
00:55:59,000 --> 00:56:01,000
See, I don't like Dr. Pepper,

1379
00:56:01,000 --> 00:56:03,000
but I will live and die for all-dressed chips.

1380
00:56:03,000 --> 00:56:05,000
Outnumbered. Finally, finally!

1381
00:56:05,000 --> 00:56:07,000
I'm not Canadian enough.

1382
00:56:07,000 --> 00:56:09,000
No.

1383
00:56:09,000 --> 00:56:11,000
Dang.

1384
00:56:11,000 --> 00:56:13,000
This is where Russ can't read his writing.

1385
00:56:13,000 --> 00:56:15,000
We run into this problem a lot.

1386
00:56:15,000 --> 00:56:17,000
And sometimes he's like,

1387
00:56:17,000 --> 00:56:19,000
don't look at my book, and I'm like,

1388
00:56:19,000 --> 00:56:21,000
as if I could read it.

1389
00:56:21,000 --> 00:56:23,000
No worries.

1390
00:56:23,000 --> 00:56:25,000
Whoa.

1391
00:56:25,000 --> 00:56:27,000
Can you change my mind with a really good perception rule?

1392
00:56:27,000 --> 00:56:29,000
Maybe.

1393
00:56:29,000 --> 00:56:31,000
Not likely. Let's see.

1394
00:56:31,000 --> 00:56:33,000
Hope he's like, change my mind.

1395
00:56:33,000 --> 00:56:35,000
Sure can't. Just roll this.

1396
00:56:35,000 --> 00:56:37,000
Make me believe.

1397
00:56:37,000 --> 00:56:39,000
Where is it? It's there somewhere.

1398
00:56:39,000 --> 00:56:41,000
It's a one.

1399
00:56:41,000 --> 00:56:43,000
I saw a seven.

1400
00:56:43,000 --> 00:56:45,000
It wasn't a seven.

1401
00:56:45,000 --> 00:56:47,000
It was, in fact, a one.

1402
00:56:47,000 --> 00:56:49,000
All gardens look the same covered in vomit.

1403
00:56:49,000 --> 00:56:51,000
That's the saying, right?

1404
00:56:51,000 --> 00:56:53,000
I'm pretty sure.

1405
00:56:53,000 --> 00:56:55,000
You got it.

1406
00:56:55,000 --> 00:56:57,000
It's deep.

1407
00:56:57,000 --> 00:56:59,000
I can't remember his real name now.

1408
00:56:59,000 --> 00:57:01,000
Baron von Mare.

1409
00:57:01,000 --> 00:57:03,000
Jasek.

1410
00:57:03,000 --> 00:57:05,000
Mare Baron.

